nicBusType.name: nicBusType
nicBusType.description: Bus type of the network interface card.. Refer to the following definitions; value contens 0 other 1 isa 2 eisa 3 pci

nicSegment.name: nicSegment
nicSegment.description: Segment number of the network interface card.

nicBusNumber.name: nicBusNumber
nicBusNumber.description: Bus number of the network interface card.

nicDeviceNumber.name: nicDeviceNumber
nicDeviceNumber.description: Device number of the network interface card.

nicFunction.name: nicFunction
nicFunction.description: Function number of the network interface card.

nicMACAddress.name: nicMACAddress
nicMACAddress.description: The interface address of the physical layer of the network interface card.

nicSpeed.name: nicSpeed
nicSpeed.description: Ratings speed of network interface card.(unit:Mbit/s)

nicTransmissionTotalPacket.name: nicTransmissionTotalPacket
nicTransmissionTotalPacket.description: The total number of packets that higher-level protocols requested be transmitted to a subnetwork-unicast address; including those that were discarded or not sent.

nicTransmissionTotalByte.name: nicTransmissionTotalByte
nicTransmissionTotalByte.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the interface; including framing characters.

nicDeferredXmits.name: nicDeferredXmits
nicDeferredXmits.description: A count of frames for which the first transmission attempt on a particular interface is delayed because the medium is busy.

nicSingleCollisions.name: nicSingleCollisions
nicSingleCollisions.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames on a particular interface for which transmission is inhibited by exactly one collision.

nicMultipleCollisions.name: nicMultipleCollisions
nicMultipleCollisions.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames on a particular interface for which transmission is inhibited by more than one collision.

nicExcessiveCollisions.name: nicExcessiveCollisions
nicExcessiveCollisions.description: A count of frames for which transmission on a particular interface fails due to excessive collisions.

nicCarrierSenceErrors.name: nicCarrierSenceErrors
nicCarrierSenceErrors.description: The number of times that the carrier sense condition was lost or never asserted when attempting to transmit a frame on a particular interface.

nicLateCollisionErrors.name: nicLateCollisionErrors
nicLateCollisionErrors.description: The number of times that a collision is detected on a particular interface later than 512 bit-times into the transmission of a packet.

nicSQETestErrors.name: nicSQETestErrors
nicSQETestErrors.description: A count of times that the SQE TEST ERROR message is generated by the PLS sublayer for a particular interface. The SQE TEST ERROR message is defined in section 7.2.2.2.4 of ANSI/IEEE 802.3-1985 and its generation is described in section 7.2.4.6 of the same document.

nicMACXmitsErrors.name: nicMACXmitsErrors
nicMACXmitsErrors.description: A count of frames for which transmission on a particular interface fails due to an internal MAC sublayer transmit error. A frame is only counted by an instance of this object if it is not counted by the corresponding instance of either the dot3StatsLateCollisions object; the dot3StatsExcessiveCollisions object; or the dot3StatsCarrierSenseErrors object.

nicReceiveTotalPacket.name: nicReceiveTotalPacket
nicReceiveTotalPacket.description: The number of subnetwork-unicast packets delivered to a higher-layer protocol.

nicReceiveTotalByte.name: nicReceiveTotalByte
nicReceiveTotalByte.description: The total number of octets received on the interface; including framing characters.

nicFCSErrors.name: nicFCSErrors
nicFCSErrors.description: A count of frames received on a particular interface that are an integral number of octets in length but do not pass the FCS check.

nicAlignmentErrors.name: nicAlignmentErrors
nicAlignmentErrors.description: A count of frames received on a particular interface that are not an integral number of octets in length and do not pass the FCS check.

nicFrameTooLong.name: nicFrameTooLong
nicFrameTooLong.description: A count of frames received on a particular interface that exceed the maximum permitted frame size.

nicMACReceiveErrors.name: nicMACReceiveErrors
nicMACReceiveErrors.description: A count of frames for which reception on a particular interface fails due to an internal MAC sublayer receive error. A frame is only counted by an instance of this object if it is not counted by the corresponding instance of either the dot3StatsFrameTooLongs object; the dot3StatsAlignmentErrors object; or the dot3StatsFCSErrors object.
